The paper discusses the use of evidential neural networks (ENN) to model uncertainty in classification tasks. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, given that the paper focuses on the use of neural networks for classification tasks, cs.AI and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The use of ENNs in computer vision applications may also make cs.CV a likely sub-category. The other two sub-categories, cs.NE and cs.SI, are less likely but still possible given the use of neural networks and the potential applications in social and information networks.
